'''Boxing out''' is a term used to describe a technique used in [[basketball]] to obtain [[rebound (basketball)|rebounds]]. A player boxes out another player by positioning himself between the other player and the basket; he or she then uses their buttocks to push the other player away, thereby gaining an advantegous position over the oppossing team's rebounder. The action can also be called "blocking out" or "butting-out".

Box out is also a dating term.  See: [[Boxing-out]]

